1971: the following two matches are often listed as having been played for
      the Copa Lipton but this is incorrect, they were 'normal' friendlies.

14 Jul Buenos Aires       Argentina 1-0 Uruguay
18 Jul Montevideo         Uruguay   1-1 Argentina


Copa Lipton 1973

17 May Buenos Aires       Argentina 1-1 Uruguay

As visiting team, Uruguay won the trophy.


Copa Lipton 1976

 8 Apr Buenos Aires       Argentina 4-1 Uruguay

NB: also counted for the Copa del Atlántico 1976.


Copa Lipton 1992

23 Sep Montevideo         Uruguay   0-0 Argentina

As visiting team, Argentina won the trophy.


Match Details

Copa Thomas Lipton 1905

15-08-1905  Argentina   0-0   Uruguay Stadium: Sociedad Sportiva (Buenos Aires)

    They played overtime, the first half for 15' and the second for 6' due 
    to lack of light.  

ARG: Laforia, Jorge Brown, Juan Domingo Brown, Eliseo Brown, Rodman, Forrester,
     Lett, Weiss, Dickinson, Frers, Moore.

URU: Cayetano Saporti, Carve, Bouton, Carbone, Rovegno, G. Stocks, A. Camacho,
     Enrique Peña, Hernández, Cuadra, Rincón.

 
Copa Thomas Lipton 1906

15-08-1906  Uruguay     0-2   Argentina

      [Arnoldo Watson Hutton, Eliseo Brown]

URU: Cayetano Saporiti, Bertone, Apesteguy, Sanderson, Carve, Branda,
     Michelerena, Sumarán, Peralta, G. Stocks, Enrique Peña.

ARG: Coulthurs, Juan Domingo Brown, Jorge Brown, Buchanan, Eliseo Brown,
     Dickinson, Hemman, Browne, Arnoldo Watson Hutton.

  
Copa Thomas Lipton 1910

15-08-1910  Uruguay     3-1   Argentina   Stadium: Belvedere (Cancha de Wanderers), Montevideo

      [Pablo Dacal 22, Pedro Zibechi 49, Carlos Scarone 63 ; Juan Enrique Hayes 71]

URU: Cayetano Saporiti (Wanderers); Juan Carlos Bertone (Cap.) (Wanderers),
     José Benincasa (River Plate); Jorge G. Pacheco (Nacional), Oscar Sanz
     (River Plate), Juan Pena (Nacional); Vicente Módena (River Plate), Pablo
     Dacal (River Plate), José Piendibene (CURCC), Carlos Scarone (CURCC),
     Pedro Zibechi (CURCC).

ARG: Carlos T. Wilson (San Isidro); Jorge Gibson Brown (Cap.) (Alumni), Juan
     Domingo Brown (Alumni); Ernesto Alejandro Brown (Alumni), Armando Ginocchio
     (Newell's Old Boys), Haroldo M. Grant (Belgrano); Elías Fernández (River
     Plate); Maximiliano Susan (Estudiantes de Buenos Aires), Juan Enrique
     Hayes (Rosario Central), Arnoldo P. Watson Hutton (Alumni), José Viale 
     (Newell's Old Boys).

Ref: León Peyrou 
Attendance: 8.000

  
